40:29.880 --> 40:32.474
Fuck, no! Fuck...

40:34.560 --> 40:36.232
No, I can't let ya!

40:37.240 --> 40:40.835
Come on, I can't let ya! I can't let ya!

40:40.920 --> 40:43.514
- What the fuck you doing?
- Give me a lift, will ya?

40:43.600 --> 40:46.672
I'm trying to save him from himself.
The drop-off man says it's pure.

40:46.760 --> 40:48.671
<i>- Fuck, no!
- Get off!</i>

40:50.360 --> 40:52.828
BABY CRYING

40:57.560 --> 41:00.836
You know, they say that tobacco
is the hardest habit to kick.

41:02.480 --> 41:04.198
It's mine! It's mine!

41:04.280 --> 41:05.998
How could you, Dad?

41:06.080 --> 41:08.958
At least we know
what's up with him now.

41:09.040 --> 41:13.272
(Jamie) A dealer never touches his own
stock. Isn't that what you've always said?

41:13.360 --> 41:17.751
- Dad!
- You think after all these years clean

41:17.840 --> 41:19.990
I woke up one morning and thought,

41:20.080 --> 41:23.277
"Why don't I stick a needle
in my vein and taste my own wares?"

41:23.360 --> 41:24.918
This was done to me!

41:26.160 --> 41:27.149
By who?

41:28.200 --> 41:29.519
<i>Fuck off!</i>

41:29.600 --> 41:32.717
Fuck off, the lot of youse!
None of your fucking business!

41:32.800 --> 41:35.234
Fuck the lot of youse!

41:35.320 --> 41:38.118
How dare you question me?

41:38.200 --> 41:40.794
Stop your fucking gawping!

41:40.880 --> 41:44.509
You fucking...

41:51.680 --> 41:52.590
Get away!

42:03.720 --> 42:06.075
I'm telling you - 20 seconds max.

42:06.160 --> 42:08.116
You'd never know they'd been touched.

42:08.200 --> 42:09.235
Mm-hm.

42:09.320 --> 42:12.198
WPC Donnelly,
you are a bloody legend!

42:12.280 --> 42:15.670
Oi! We're all constables now.
You sexist prick.

42:15.760 --> 42:19.514
Debbie, Mr Watsford says he needs
that 15 quid before the weekend.

42:19.600 --> 42:22.319
- Right. Come on, I'm having a go.
- Are you?

42:22.400 --> 42:25.312
- Good luck.
- Good luck?

42:25.400 --> 42:27.868
- Don't need luck.
- You need a steady hand.

42:30.120 --> 42:31.678
Where'd you get that from?

42:33.840 --> 42:36.274
What about credit for your mobile?

42:39.480 --> 42:41.277
<i>(Mandy) So who's gonna run things?</i>

42:43.000 --> 42:44.353
Dad can't.

42:44.440 --> 42:48.399
I suppose it's left to my lad over here
to step up and show his mettle.

42:48.480 --> 42:51.358
He's creative, handy, flexible.

42:51.440 --> 42:53.715
With respect, Kelly...

42:53.800 --> 42:55.711
Dad doesn't do interior design.

42:59.520 --> 43:01.431
I'm taking over.

43:01.520 --> 43:03.476
(Kelly) Eldest son succeeds.
Fucking typical!

43:03.560 --> 43:06.074
Do you have a problem with that, Shane?

43:06.160 --> 43:10.199
To be honest, babe, I just want to be free
to invest me energies in other stuff.

43:10.280 --> 43:13.397
Trafficking body parts.
That's where the serious money is.

43:13.480 --> 43:15.118
See?

43:15.200 --> 43:16.918
Visionary.

43:17.000 --> 43:18.752
You said nothing could draw you back.

43:18.840 --> 43:21.115
Don't make me explain myself, Mand.

43:22.600 --> 43:24.750
Your livelihood comes from this business.

43:25.840 --> 43:28.991
Would you rather I stuck to me word
and you and Katie go without?

43:29.080 --> 43:30.991
- (Katie) Mummy!
- I'm coming.

43:31.080 --> 43:32.911
(Micky) What about the Dudnics?

43:33.640 --> 43:35.631
<i>No need to worry about them any more.</i>

43:47.040 --> 43:50.271
Well, I want you two round this table
tomorrow morning, eight o'clock.

43:51.360 --> 43:56.115
We'll be talking business models
and enforcement. OK?

43:57.240 --> 43:59.595
- OK?
- Uh-huh.

44:10.120 --> 44:11.678
<i>(Jamie) There's a Spanish proverb</i>

44:11.760 --> 44:14.593
<i>says an ounce of blood is worth
more than a pound of friendship.</i>

44:14.680 --> 44:17.990
<i>Being part of a family
isn't always easy.</i>

44:18.080 --> 44:20.071
<i>It can be unpleasant.</i>

44:21.240 --> 44:24.835
<i>There's rivalry, resentment,
feeling stifled.</i>

44:29.560 --> 44:32.791
<i>They can disappoint you, disgust you.</i>

44:32.880 --> 44:34.757
<i>But you never give up on them.</i>

44:35.880 --> 44:40.271
<i>You'll sacrifice your own wants
and needs because, like it or not,</i>

44:40.360 --> 44:42.874
<i>you're tied to the tossers for life.</i>

44:46.400 --> 44:48.834
<i>Friends and lovers may come and go</i>

44:48.920 --> 44:51.514
<i>but the clan remains.</i>

45:37.960 --> 45:39.712
What dainty dishes

45:39.800 --> 45:45.636
will the weary manny feast from before
quenching the most arid of thirsts?

45:46.560 --> 45:48.471
Sod all, that's what.

45:56.160 --> 45:57.639
HE FARTS

46:00.120 --> 46:02.236
HE GROANS

46:02.320 --> 46:04.470
- All right, Frank?
- Yes, mate.

